<% if sessions.any? %>
  <%# Beta 4 — FB-14 (2026-05-20): the bulk-revoke `[revoke]` action
      no longer renders on its own row above the table. Instead it
      lives INSIDE the `<thead>` row, replacing the column labels
      when at least one row is selected. The column-1 select-all
      checkbox stays put.

      Beta 4 — FB-116 (2026-05-20): swapped the header from a single
      colspan-spanning cell with inline spans (which broke column→
      data alignment per FB-108) to TWO co-existing `<tr>` rows in
      `<thead>` — `defaultHeader` (per-column `<th>` cells matching
      the body grid) and `actionHeader` (checkbox + colspan action
      bar). The Stimulus controller flips the `hidden` attribute on
      whichever row is inactive. Per-column headers now align over
      their body columns. %>

  <%# Beta 4 — Phase F3-DEEP-B (2026-05-20):
      Migrated to the canonical `.tui-table` styling family that ships
      with `Tui::TableComponent` (F2 primitive). Approach B — class
      swap on the existing markup, no component refactor — keeps the
      bulk-revoke + checkbox + chip + sortable-header logic intact
      while inheriting the TUI table grammar (hairline rows, muted
      lowercase headers, no zebra, no hover).

      Beta 4 — FB-50 (2026-05-20): column rework. Previous columns
      were checkbox / user-agent / pinged (3 cols). New layout is
      checkbox / device / browser / ip / last seen / created (6 cols).
      The raw `user_agent` string is projected via
      `Formatting::UserAgent.device(...)` + `.browser(...)` to a
      small enumerated set. The IP `TooltipBadgeComponent` is gone —
      it's a plain cell now. "pinged" renamed to "last seen". A new
      "created" column shows session-creation relative time.

      Beta 4 — Phase F3-C (2026-05-20):
        * Row + header checkboxes use `Tui::CheckboxComponent` form
          mode. The stimulus targets + `data-current` host element
          live on the enclosing `<span class="sessions-table__checkbox">`
          wrapper.
        * The current-session marker uses `Tui::ChipComponent
          variant: :current` per ADR 0016 and sits in the device
          column for visibility.

      Sortable headers drive `?sessions_sort=<key>&sessions_dir=
      <asc|desc>` on `/settings` itself. %>
  <table class="tui-table sessions-table" style="table-layout: auto;">
    <thead>
      <%# FB-116 — Default header: per-column `<th>` cells, matching the
          body's column grid one-to-one so labels sit directly above
          their data. FB-108 alignment: text columns (device/browser/
          ip) get `--left`, date columns (last seen/created) get
          `--right` (which also stamps tabular-nums). %>
      <tr data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="defaultHeader">
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--left col-action">
          <span class="sessions-table__checkbox sessions-table__checkbox--header"
                data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="headerCheckbox"
                data-action="change->sessions-bulk-revoke#toggleAll">
            <%= render(Tui::CheckboxComponent.new(name: "__select_all", value: "yes", checked: false)) %>
          </span>
        </th>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--left sortable sessions-table__col-device">
          <%= helpers.sort_link_to("device", "user_agent", current_sort: sessions_sort, current_dir: sessions_dir, sort_param: "sessions_sort", dir_param: "sessions_dir") %>
        </th>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--left sortable sessions-table__col-browser">browser</th>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--left sortable sessions-table__col-ip">ip</th>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--right num sortable sessions-table__col-last-seen">
          <%= helpers.sort_link_to("last seen", "last_activity", current_sort: sessions_sort, current_dir: sessions_dir, sort_param: "sessions_sort", dir_param: "sessions_dir") %>
        </th>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--right num sortable sessions-table__col-created">created</th>
      </tr>
      <%# FB-116 — Action header: shown only when ≥1 row is selected.
          Checkbox `<th>` stays in column 1; columns 2..N collapse
          into a single `<th colspan="5">` carrying the counter +
          [revoke] link. The Stimulus controller flips `hidden` on
          whichever <tr> is inactive so only one is visible at a
          time. %>
      <tr data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="actionHeader" hidden>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--left col-action"></th>
        <th class="tui-table__th tui-table__th--left sessions-table__header-swap" colspan="5"
            data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="headerCell">
          <span class="sessions-table__header-actions" data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="actions">
            <span class="sessions-table__counter" data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="counter">0 selected</span>
            <a data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="link" class="bracketed-muted">[revoke]</a>
          </span>
        </th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <% sessions.each do |s| %>
        <tr class="tui-table__row" data-tui-cursor-target="row">
          <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--left col-action">
            <span class="sessions-table__checkbox"
                  data-sessions-bulk-revoke-target="checkbox"
                  data-action="change->sessions-bulk-revoke#toggle"
                  data-current="<%= current_flag(s) %>"
                  data-value="<%= s.id %>">
              <%= render(Tui::CheckboxComponent.new(name: "ids[]", value: s.id, checked: false)) %>
            </span>
          </td>
          <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--left sessions-table__cell-device">
            <%= Formatting::UserAgent.device(s.user_agent.to_s) %><% if current?(s) %> <%= render(Tui::ChipComponent.new(label: "this", variant: :current)) %><% end %>
          </td>
          <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--left sessions-table__cell-browser">
            <%= Formatting::UserAgent.browser(s.user_agent.to_s) %>
          </td>
          <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--left sessions-table__cell-ip">
            <%= s.ip.presence || "—" %>
          </td>
          <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num sessions-table__cell-last-seen"><%= helpers.compact_time_ago(s.last_activity_at) %></td>
          <td class="tui-table__td tui-table__td--right num sessions-table__cell-created"><%= helpers.compact_time_ago(s.created_at) %></td>
        </tr>
      <% end %>
    </tbody>
  </table>
<% else %>
  <p class="text-muted" style="margin: 0;">no active sessions.</p>
<% end %>
